Class TMSMapLayer

Deprecated. 

@Deprecated
public class TMSMapLayer
extends RasterLayer

A raster layer class that uses an URL as a source for the map tile data. The request are generated in this manner:

baseUrl + zoom + separator + x + separator + y + format

For example if: baseUrl = "http://tile.openstreetmap.org/", separator = "/", format = ".png"

"http://tile.openstreetmap.org/" + "0" + "/" + "0" + "/" + "0" + ".png"

Result: http://tile.openstreetmap.org/0/0/0.png

Deprecated. 
Class constructor. Creates a new raster layer that uses a specified URL as a source for the tile data. Tiles that are out of the specified minimum / maximum zoom range are not downloaded. The id used should be unique to each rasterlayer, if two or more raster layers use the same id, they will also share the tiles in the cache. Supported image formats are .jpg and .png. Note: by default is based on "OSM tile schema", with flipped Y coordinate, change it using setTmsY()

Parameters:
projection - the desired projection
minZoom - the minimum zoom
maxZoom - the maximum zoom
id - unique layer id. Id for the layer must be depend ONLY on the layer source, otherwise tile caching will not work properly.
baseUrl - the base URL
separator - the seperator for the URL
format - the image format for the url

setTmsY

public void setTmsY(boolean tmsY)
Deprecated. 
Use this to set that Y axis is according to TMS standard, ie with origin in southeast. Otherwise it is in northeast, like in common public servers: OpenStreetMap and others

Parameters:
tmsY - true if TMS standard Y orientation is needed. Default is false

fetchTile

public void fetchTile(MapTile tile)
Deprecated. 
Description copied from class: RasterLayer
Start appropriate task for fetching the requested tile. This gets called when a visible tile can't be found in any of the caches and thus must be reloaded from the source. Inheriting classes can either start a new task immediately or wait for the flush command to start all at once. NB! You need to start the task in your implementation, it is not done automatically. If you have online tiles then usually you calculate your URL (urlString) and the following line is the last one in your implementation: components.rasterTaskPool.execute(new NetFetchTileTask(tile, components, tileIdOffset, urlString));

Overrides:
fetchTile in class RasterLayer
Parameters:
tile - the requested tile

flush

public void flush()
Deprecated. 
Description copied from class: RasterLayer
Flushes the currently pending tiles list. Gets called every time the screen changes and all the tiles that have to be fetched have been determined. Implementing this is not required, if the fetchTile method starts the appropriate tasks itself.
